PostgreSQL - Database management system using SQL language (Structured Query Language)

Relational Database - each table is realated to one another (one table has name of client thier address and another table has their online order)

RDMS - Relational Database management system. Such as MYSQL SQLlite PostgreSQL

PGadmin - software that manages PostgreSQL

Table - table is an object is realted to a key. with recors of rows and columns

Null - blank record in a table 

Field - a column in the table designed to maintain specific information about every record in the table

Record - a row of data consist of individual entry that exists in a table. Example of a record is all the data about a particular CUSTOMER

Column - a vertical entity in a table containing all information associated with a specific field in a table.
For example, a column in the CUSTOMERS table is ADDRESS, which represents location description and would be as shown below


Constraints
Not Null - Ensure that a column cannot ahv ea null value

Default - Provides a default value for a column when none is specified

Unique - prevents two records from having identical values in a particular column

primary key - uniquely idenf
